    "updated_at": "2014-11-09T05:21:40Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "\"Flip over\" is a good metaphor, though depending on the user and goal, a hybrid showing the code/data being changed when visual changes occur would be even better.\n\nOther examples of user efforts that could be persisted as input, not widget-like:\n- cell metadata editing\n  - [jsoneditor](https://github.com/josdejong/jsoneditor/)\n    - good roundtrip\n- code cell editing\n  - visual programming\n    - [blockly](https://code.google.com/p/blockly/)\n      - can do output javascript and python\n      - \"native\" format is semi-gnarly XML\n      - little roundtrip capability\n  - variable editing\n    - [handsontable](https://github.com/handsontable/jquery-handsontable)\n      - pretty good roundtrip\n    - also json editor\n- markdown cell editing\n  - image/figure editing\n    - [svg-edit](https://code.google.com/p/svg-edit/)\n      - good roundtrip, i guess\n    - [nomnoml](http://www.nomnoml.com/)\n      - no real roundtrip\n  - rich text editing\n    - [scribe](https://github.com/guardian/scribe) or [quill](https://github.com/quilljs/quill)\n"
  },
